The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Friday, May 4, 2007

 School festival

 Spic-Macay inter-school fest at Mahadevi Birla Girls Higher Secondary School, 9 am. The fest is organised in association with Laxmipat Singhania Academy, Apeejay School, Mahadevi Birla Girls School, St Thomas School and others.

 On screen

 Inaugural ceremony of Festival of Films from Assam, with focus on Bodo cinema, at Sisir Mancha, 4 pm.

 Furniture

 Furniture Bazaar 2007 at Ice Skating Rink, 11 am to 8 pm.

 Book fair

 An exhibition of books and pamphlets on Rabindranath Tagore, at Rabindra Charcha Bhavan, 2 pm to 8 pm.

 Stagecraft

 Tagoreana, a programme of songs and readings from Tagores creations, at Dakshin Kolikata Samsad, Poolside Banquet, 7.30 pm.

 Rituranga, a symphony of seasons by Sapphire Creations Dance, at Padatiks Buildwell Theatre, 6.30 pm.

 Pret show

 An exhibition of summer and holiday wear by Ravage, at 85 Lansdowne, 85 B Sarat Bose Road, 11 am-7 pm. 

 Suti, an exhibition of handwoven cotton saris, at Kanishkas from 10.30 am to 8 pm. 

 Art watch

 Sculpture 2000-2006, by Sankho Chaudhuri, at Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, 2 pm to 8 pm.

 Paintings by Samik De, at Chemould Art Gallery, 2 pm to 7 pm.




